  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[HTML link in Twig]]></title>
    <link href="http://drupal8notes.github.io/html-link-in-twig/"/>
    <updated>2014-11-05T00:45:59-05:00</updated>
    <id>http://drupal8notes.github.io/html-link-in-twig</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In Drupal 7, you could use the <code>array('html' =&gt; TRUE)</code> parameter to make an HTML link. Here&rsquo;s how to do it in Twig.</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>{{ link(title, url.setOption('html', true)) }}</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Note that url should be an instance of <code>\Drupal\Core\Url</code>.</p>
]]></content>
  </entry>
  
